cp bashrc /storage/.bashrc

If UBUNTU/vdr.sh includes exit 0 (no vdr start), call ./ubuntu.sh to
mount all chroot directories (for testing purpose)

cat /sys/class/amhdmitx/amhdmitx0/disp_cap > /storage/.kodi/userdata/disp_cap

As an example:
cp disp_cap /storage/.kodi/userdata

cp advancedsettings.xml /storage/.kodi/userdata